JOE & THE JUICE App Privacy Policy
Introduction
At JOE & THE JUICE A/S ("JOE &THE JUICE", "we", "us" or "our") we givehigh priority to confidentiality and data security. This privacy policy appliesto our processing of personal data collected through your use of our app andestablishes guidelines for the way JOE & THE JUICE processes your personaldata and provides you with the information that you are entitled to receiveunder applicable data protection laws. You should read the privacy policy beforeyou hand over your personal data to JOE & THE JUICE.
1. Data controller
The data controller of your personal dataprocessed through JOE & THE JUICE’s app is:
JOE & THE JUICE A/S Address: Østergade26,
1100 København K
CVR-no.: 26589355
Email:
privacy@joejuice.com
2. In-app data and web-app cookies
Types of personal data JOE & THE JUICEuses the mobile-app as well as cookies on web-app to collect, and thisconnection processes, your personal data. JOE & THE JUICE may collect thefollowing personal data about you, when you use our app:
IP address and MAC address
Device ID and device type
Operating system and version
Browser type and screen resolution
Device manufacturer and model
Geo-location
Language
Interaction with QR codes
Use of loyalty cards
Number, type and frequency of products you purchase through the     app
Sections visited within the app
Redemption of loyalty cards and gift cards made available     through the app
Products you have searched for
Information about your use of our web-app, including     click-behaviour, the website or app that referred you to our app, the     functionality of the app while you use it
Time and date of your use of the app
The content you view and features you access, entered search     terms and personal information you make available to us via a social media     platform, such as by clicking on a social media icon linked from our     website.
We use our mobile-app and cookies via theweb-app to collect the above-mentioned personal data.
The purposes of the process
Your personal data may be processed for thefollowing purposes:
Marketing and advertising, including to promote our products     and brand
Product and service development
Statistics and analysis, including to understand how you     interact with the app and to improve the app
Legal basis for processing
JOE & THE JUICE processes your personaldata on the following basis:
Legitimate interests:
We base the processing of     your personal data on our legitimate interests in, for example, conducting     statistics, analyses, as well as improving and developing our products and     services (Article 6(1)(f) of the General Data Protection Regulation).
Consent:
We only process and     disclose personal data to third parties collected through cookies via the     web-app if you give your prior consent to it through the cookie consent     solution on the web-app (Article 6(1)(a) of the General Data Protection     Regulation). You can always withdraw your consent by contacting us as     described below or by changing your cookie consent as described in our     cookie policy. However, withdrawing your consent does not affect the     legality of the processing that preceded the withdrawal.
Retention period
Personal data collected through our JOE& THE JUICE mobile-app is being stored for as long as you are active on theapp (e.g. when you make purchases via the mobile- or web-app). As a generalrule, your account will be considered "inactive" if you have not madea purchase for more than 2 years (3 years if you have purchased a loyalty card)whereafter your account and personal data will be deleted subsequently.
Personal data which forms part ofbookkeeping material is, however, kept for 10 years from the end of the currentfinancial year to ensure compliance with the legal obligations set out inbookkeeping legislation (cf. Article 6(1)(c) of the General Data ProtectionRegulation).
Cookies are deleted in accordance with ourcookie policy, which is available via the following link https://www.joejuice.com/policy/cookie-policy.Personal data collected through cookies may, however, be processed for up to ayear after collection.
However, the information may be stored fora longer period in anonymised form.
3. If you use the chat
Types of personal data
When you use the chat in the app, JOE &THE JUICE collects and processes your personal data. JOE & THE JUICEcollects, processes, and stores the following types of your personal data:
Your user information, including your email address
What your inquiry is about
Date of your inquiry
Other information you provide in connection with your inquiry.
We encourage you not to provide sensitive personal data such as     health information (e.g. allergies or religion) to us. You are, however,     welcome to submit preferences for food and beverages.
The objectives of the process
Your personal data will be processed forthe following purposes:
Handling of your inquiry/request
General communication
Statistics and analysis
Legal basis for processing
JOE & THE JUICE processes your personaldata on the below-mentioned bases. The basis depends on the nature of yourinquiry.
Legitimate interests:
We may     process your personal data on the basis of our legitimate interests in     handling your inquiry, communicating with you, and developing our products     and services (Article 6(1)(f) of the General Data Protection Regulation).
Disclosure
We may disclose your personal data toexternal suppliers or other relevant JOE & THE JUICE entities who, inagreement with us, make sure to provide the service you order. The disclosureis based on our legitimate interest in being able to provide the service youare requesting (Article 6(1)(f) of the General Data Protection Regulation).
Retention period
Your personal data related to the specificinquiry will be stored for 1 year from your inquiry has been marked as closed.Personal data which forms part of bookkeeping material is, however, kept for 10years from the end of the current financial year to ensure compliance with thelegal obligations set out in bookkeeping legislation (cf. Article 6(1)(c) ofthe General Data Protection Regulation). Personal data can be stored for alonger period in anonymised form.
If you are a customer or an employee of oneof our customers, suppliers, or other business partners, we refer to thesection below.
4. When you register as a user
Types of personal data
When you register as a user in the app, JOE& THE JUICE processes your personal data. JOE & THE JUICE may collect,process, and store the following types of your personal data:
Your name
Your date of birth
Your email address, Facebook ID, Google login information or     Apple ID (if you use one of these services to log in)
Your telephone number (including for SMS marketing if consent     is provided)
Your gender
Country
Loyalty points
The purposes of the process
Your personal data will be processed forthe following purposes:
Management of user account/profile
Authentication and fraud prevention using a one-way hash of     your phone number
To customise your user account to you
To customise offers to you if you have consented to receiving     marketing material, including SMS marketing, or if we are allowed to promote     our products without your consent
promote our products without your consent
Statistics and analysis
Legal basis for processing
JOE & THE JUICE processes your personaldata on the following bases:
Legitimate interests:
We process     your information based on our legitimate interest in managing the created     user accounts, as well as our legitimate interest in conducting statistics     and analysis, and customising our platform and marketing material to you     (Article 6(1)(f) of the General Data Protection Regulation).
Consent:
If you have provided your     consent, we may also use your telephone number for SMS marketing (Article     6(1)(a) of the GDPR).
Retention period
Your personal data will be stored until youdelete your account. However, data related to marketing consent will beretained until you withdraw your consent or delete your account. Additionally,the data can be stored for a longer period in anonymised form.
