8. Disclosure to other data controllersand outsourcing to data processors
To achieve the above purposes, we may givethird parties access to your personal data, which, based on a contractualrelationship with JOE & THE JUICE, provides relevant services, this couldbe IT suppliers or other suppliers that process personal data for us. Suchsuppliers will only process personal data in accordance with our instructionsaccording to the signed data processing agreements.
In the context of JOE & THE JUICE'sdevelopment, the corporate structure may change, e.g., by the total or partialsale of the company. In the case of a partial transfer of assets containingpersonal data, the processing basis for the related transfer of personal datais, as a rule, Article 6(1)(f) of the General Data Protection Regulation, sinceJOE & THE JUICE has an interest in transferring parts of its assets andmaking commercial/structural changes.
In addition to what is described above,your personal data is generally not disclosed to a third party without yourconsent. However, in certain circumstances, it may be necessary to discloseyour personal data to e.g. the police, lawyers, accountants, courts, otherpublic authorities, potential buyers and group-linked companies. We do thisbased on your consent and our legitimate interests.
Your personal data may be transferred todata processors or data controllers established in countries outside the EU/EEAthat do not have an adequate level of protection. Such transfers will only takeplace once a transfer tool is secured. The transfers will be based on the EUCommission's standard contractual clauses or binding corporate rules, which youhave a right of access to. If you have any questions about the tools fortransfers to countries outside the EU/EEA please contact us at privacy@joejuice.com.
9. Your rights
You have the right to access the personal data we process about     you
You have the right to object to our collection and further     processing of your personal data
You have the right to rectification and deletion of your     personal data, however there are certain statutory exceptions, including     the Bookkeeping Act
You have the right to ask us to restrict the processing of your     personal data
In certain circumstances, you may also request to receive a     copy of your personal data and to transmit the personal data you have     provided to us to another data controller (data portability)
You can withdraw any consents you may have given at any time.     We will then delete your personal data unless we may continue the     processing on another basis. You can cancel our newsletter by clicking on     the link at the bottom of the newsletter
10. Your rights as a California Resident
Persons with disabilities may obtain thisnotice in alternative format. Please send your request to:privacy@joejuice.com.
In addition to the information that hasbeen provided in this Privacy Policy regarding JOE & THE JUICE’s processingof personal information, and the purposes for which they are processed,Californian state laws (CCPA (CPRA)) requires JOE & THE JUICE to provideCalifornian Residents, hereunder “customers”, current and former “employees”and third-party associated “employees”, the following to information regardingtheir privacy rights.
You can see the categories of informationwe collect in the “
Types of personal data”
sections above.
Please note that there may be circumstancesin which JOE & THE JUICE is not required or permitted under applicable lawto address your request or exercise of your right. Only you or an authorizedagent that you authorize to act on your behalf may make a request related toyour personal information. We cannot respond to a request or provide you accessto personal information if we cannot verify your identity or authority to makea request and confirm the personal information that relates to you.
10.1 Right to Access to/to Know yourpersonal Information
You may have the right to request access toyour personal information and information pertaining to the source of thatpersonal information, the purposes for which we collect it, and the categoriesof third parties to whom we may sell, share, or disclose it to as well as whatpersonal information we sell, share or disclose to set third parties.
As stated by law, you can make anAccess/Know request twice a year (2 times every 12 month) free of charge.
10.2 Right to Request Deletion of YourPersonal Information
In addition to your right to gain access toyour personal data, you may also have the right to request that JOE & THEJUICE delete personal data that we have collected pertaining to you. Pleasenote that certain information may be exempt from such requests under otherlaws, such as personal information that is part of bookkeeping and accountingmaterial.
The personal information that we may stillretain is information pertaining to:
a) protecting our business, systems, andusers from fraudulent activity, b) our contractional obligations to you, c)addressing technical issues that impair existing functionality, d) necessaryfor us, or others, to exercise their free speech or other rights, e) complywith law enforcement requests pursuant to lawful process, f) for scientific orhistorical research, g) for our own internal purposes reasonably related toyour relationship with us, or to comply with legal obligations.
10.3 Right to Correct InaccuratePersonal Information
You have the right to request that JOE& THE JUICE correct inaccurate personal information about you. Thecorrection of your personal information will be done accordingly to the natureof the personal information and the purpose(s) of which the processing of thepersonal information is occurring.
10.4 Right to Limit Use and Disclosureof Sensitive Personal Information
We may collect
sensitive personalinformation
as part of your employment at or contract with JOE & THEJUICE. As a Californian Resident, you have the right to limit our use, ordisclosure, of this information to the extent that the processing or disclosureof the information is necessary in order for JOE & THE JUICE to perform theservices that we provide. Some sensitive personal information be exempt fromthe CCPA (CPRA) due to it being considered public information and willtherefore not be covered in case you should exercise this right.
The CCPA (CPRA) defines “sensitive personalinformation” as “
information that reveals a resident’s:
Government-issued identifiers
i)  Social Security,
ii)  Driver’s license,
iii)  State identification card, or
iv)  Passport number.
Finances
i)  Account log-in.
ii)  Financial account combinedwith any required security or access code, password, or credentials allowingaccess to an account.
iii)  Debit card or credit cardnumber combined with any required security or access code, password, orcredentials.
Geolocation
A resident’s precise geolocation,including address, ZIP code, and city.
Race, religion, and union membership
i)  Racial or ethnic origin,
ii)  Religious or philosophicalbeliefs, or
iii)  Union membership.
Communications
The contents of a resident’s privatecommunications, (Unless the company is the intended recipient of thecommunication.)
Genetics
A resident’s genetic data.
Biometrics
Biometric information which can uniquelyidentify a resident.
Health
Personal information collected andanalyzed concerning a resident’s health.
Sexual orientation
Personal information collected andanalyzed concerning a resident’s sex life or sexual orientation.”
10.5 Right to Opt-Out of Sale or Sharingof Personal Information to Third Parties
You have the right to request that JOE& THE JUICE stop selling or sharing your personal information (“opt-out”).JOE & THE JUICE will after you have exercised this right refrain fromselling nor sharing your personal information until such a time where you againauthorise us to do so again.
10.6 Right to Non-Discrimination/NoRetaliation Following Your Opt-Out or Exercise of Other Rights
JOE & THE JUICE will not retaliate ifyou decide to exercise any of the rights under this Policy where prohibited bylaw. You may exercise your rights by e-mailing privacy@joejuice.com.
11. Links to other websites
Our website may contain links to otherwebsites or to integrated websites. We are not responsible for the content ofother companies' websites or their practices regarding processing of personaldata. When you visit other websites, you are encouraged to read the owner'sprivacy policy, cookie policy, and other relevant policies.
12. Questions and complaints
If you have any questions about thisprivacy policy or if you wish to complain about the way we process yourpersonal data, please feel free to contact us:
